      "file": "storage-generic-buffer-core.md",
      "displayName": "storage-generic-buffer-core.md",
      "topic": "Where to introduce storage-genericity in the buffer layer (leaf vs Layer-2 algorithm) and how to surface operations. Decision: concrete Layer-3 leaves delegating to one algorithm generic over some Storage.Protocol; operation surface via concrete-Base Property.Inout accessors (not a Buffer.Linear.Operations enum, not protocol-Base). Collapses the 2×2 Heap/Inline × Copyable/~Copyable duplication; keeps .Small expressible; preserves zero-witness specialization. Validated by two SIL experiments.",
      "date": "2026-05-24",
      "status": "RECOMMENDATION",
      "statusDetail": "Decided + experimentally validated (specialization to 0 witness_method confirmed in release + cross-module, through the real Property.Inout stack); not yet implemented in production. Reuse locus decided: concrete-Base (protocol-Base would need @inlinable → documented ~Copyable miscompile path). Phased test-gated implementation path with in-package SIL recheck at Phase 3.",
      "statusRaw": "RECOMMENDATION",
      "tier": 2,
      "scope": "cross-package"
